    <section name="jbundle quick start">
      <p>
      With a few quick commands, you can have jbundle up and running:<br/>
      </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Download, unzip, and start <a href="http://karaf.apache.org">apache-karaf</a>.</li>
          <li>In karaf, type:<br/>
            <code>
            <i>karaf@root&gt;</i> shell:source mvn:org.jbundle.config/jbundle-artifacts/${project.version}/shell/setup
            </code>
          </li>
          <li>Point your broswer to <a href="http://localhost:8181">http://localhost:8181</a>.</li>
          <li>Click on the application icons to try out some of the jbundle sample apps.</li>
        </ul>
      <p>
      Note: By default, jbundle uses the derby database engine. The database will be located in your home directory at '.jbundle'.
      </p>
    </section>
